Description: A public service provided to assisted and non-assisted housing occupants offering lower cost rental accommodation to meet their housing needs.

Name: Social Housing Subsidy
Description: A public service provided to social housing owners offering subsidies for rent for assisted housing leaseholders and occupants to meet their housing needs.

Name: Social Support
Description: A public service provided to unemployed / underemployed offering financial and employment supports.
Sub-Services:
"Financial Assistance"
"Employment Assistance"
"Social Support Case Management"
"Social Support Information and Referrals"
"Crisis and Outreach Intervention"

Name: Social Support Case Management
Description: This service provides for the intake, eligibility determination, case plan preparation, case plan implementation and monitoring.

Name: Social Support Information and Referrals
Description:
This service provides additional information about the local labour market and about resources and services in the community to applicants or participants to assist them in meeting eligibility requirements or to become involved in employment measures.  This service also includes the following types of referrals to other program and service providers:
- Referrals to program partners offering LEAP Parenting Training, Basic Education, etc.
- Referrals to agencies providing programs and services external to Ontario Works.

Name: Socio-Economic Surveying & Monitoring
Description: An internal service provided to the corporation offering research and insight into the trends in the economy, demographics, and other municipal characteristics to aid in improved land use planning and policy development.

Name: Solid Waste Disposal
Description: A public service provided to Solid Waste Haulers offering disposal and incineration of solid waste

Name: Solid Waste Transfer and Processing
Description: An internal service provided to solid waste service providers offering transfer and processing of collected waste.

Name: Special Event Transit
Description: A public service provided to special event hosts offering access to transit vehicles for the transport of people.

Name: Storm Water Drainage
Description: A public service provided to property owners offering safe removal and disposal of storm water.
Sub-Services:
"Storm Water Drainage System Design & Construction"
"Storm Water Drainage System Maintenance"
"Storm Water Treatment"
"Local Drainage Improvement "
"Storm Water Drainage Infrastructure Lifecycle Management"

Name: Storm Water Drainage Infrastructure Lifecycle Management
Description: An internal service provided to storm water drainage service providers offering management and optimization of storm water drainage infrastructure over its lifespan.

Name: Storm Water Drainage System Design & Construction
Description: An internal service provided to storm water drainage service providers offering design and construction of storm water drainage systems.

Name: Storm Water Drainage System Maintenance
Description: An internal service provided to storm water drainage service providers offering maintenance of storm water drainage systems.

Name: Storm Water Treatment
Description: An internal service provided to storm water drainage service providers offering treatment of storm drainage water.

Name: Strategic Planning
Description: An internal service provided to the corporation offering a plan that sets out the vision, mission and core values of the municipality in the short- and long-term.

Name: Street Lighting
Description: A public service provided to roadway users and adjacent property owners offering lighting of streets and roadways at night and other periods of darkness.  This service also includes the lighting of other public areas.
Sub-Services:
"Installation and Replacement of Street Lighting"
"Street Lighting Operations"
"Street Lighting Maintenance"

Name: Street Lighting Asset Lifecycle Management
Description: An internal service provided to street lighting service providers offering management and optimization of street lights and appurtances over their useful life.

Name: Street Lighting Maintenance
Description: A service delivery process group identified for the purpose of defining processes.

Name: Street Lighting Operations
Description: A service delivery process group identified for the purpose of defining processes.

Name: Street Naming
Description: A public service provided to property owners fronting on a public highway offering identification of the street name, including the renaming of the street.

Name: Street Numbering
Description: A public service provided to property owners and occupants providing a civic address to property for convenient access by service providers.

Name: Substance Misuse Prevention Consultation and Assessment
Description: A public service provided to substance abusers offering advice on how to improve personal health.

Name: Substance Misuse Prevention Education
Description: A public service provided to substance abusers offering group education on how to improve personal health.

Name: Supportive Housing
Description: A public service provided to seniors offering people who only need minimal to moderate care -- such as homemaking or personal care and support - to live independently.
Sub-Services:
"Homemaking"
"Supportive Housing Placement Coordination"
"Supportive Housing Case Management"

Name: Supportive Housing Case Management
Description: A public service provided to mentally challenged individuals offering the eligibility assessment, care planning and care oversight.

Name: Supportive Housing Placement Coordination
Description: A public service provided to prospective supportive housing residents offering a placement in a supportive housing facility.

Name: Traffic Enforcement
Description: A public service provided to traffic violators offering compliance with traffic code, and safer roadways for roadway users.

Name: Traffic Flow Control
Description: A public service provided to road users offered controlled access to the roadway by vehicles, pedestrians and bicycles.
Sub-Services:
"Traffic Signalization"
"Intelligent Transportation System Operation"
"Traffic Control/Street Signs Maintenance  "
"Traffic Control Markings Maintenance"
"Traffic Engineering Support"
"School Crossing Guard"

Name: Transit
Description: A public service provided to transit riders / passengers offering a scheduled transit and Para transit trips.
Sub-Services:
"Scheduled Transit"
"Contracted Transit"
"Special Event Transit"
"Scheduled Transit Infrastructure Lifecycle Management"
"Para-Transit"

Name: Transitional Housing
Description: A public service provided to transitional housing residents offering housing that is intended to offer a supportive living environment and tools and opportunities for social and skills development. It is an intermediate step between emergency shelters and supportive housing, with limits on the length of stay.
Sub-Services:
"Domiciliary Hostel Accommodation"
"Transitional Housing Subsidy"

Name: Urban Forestry
Description: A public service provided to property owners offering access to the amenities of trees.
Sub-Services:
"Boulevard Forestry"
"Park and Open Space Forestry"

Name: Utility Locating
Description: A public service provided to utility and construction contractors / operators offering advice on the location of underground infrastructure (e.g. gas lines, water lines, buried cable, etc.) thereby allowing the contractor who is digging around the site of such buried infrastructure not to damage the infrastructure.

Name: Value for Money Auditing
Description: An internal service provided to the corporation offering monitoring of  the value for money in delivery of services to the public and internally.

Name: Victim Support and Referral
Description: A public service provided to victims and their families, and youth at risk offering referral to support service providers.

Name: Vulnerable Adults and Seniors Consultation and Assessment
Description: A public service provided to vulnerable adults and seniors offering advice on how to improve personal health.

Name: Vulnerable Adults and Seniors Health Education
Description: A public service provided to vulnerable adults and seniors offering group education on how to improve personal health.

Name: Waste & Waste Collection By-Law Enforcement
Description: A public service provided to violators of the Noise By-law offering compliance with applicable municipal regulations

Name: Water Safety Inspection
Description: A public service offering regular inspection of water sources and surface water bodies.  The main objective of the Safe Water Program is to protect public health by ensuring that drinking water meets the health-related parameters of the Ontario Drinking Water Standards.

Name: Winter Control (Road Snow and Ice Control)
Description: A public service provided to roadway users offering safe passage along roadways during winter conditions.

Name: Workplace Health, Wellness and Safety
Description: An internal service provided to the corporation and employees offering a healthy, well and a safe environment.

Name: Zoning By-Law Development
Description: An internal service provided to the corporation offering a Zoning By-Law policy for designating the purpose and general nature for which land may be used.

Name: Zoning By-Law Enforcement
Description: A public service provided to violators of the Zoning By-law offering compliance with applicable municipal regulations

Name: Zoo
Description: A public service provided to zoo visitors offering access to zoological exhibitions.

"Zoo Exhibiting and Visiting"
